BeitEnactedbytheSenateandHouseofRepresentativesinGeneralCourtconvened:
1 1 HistoricalResourcesCouncil;YouthDevelopmentCenterHistoricalMarker.
2 I. Pursuant to RSA 236:40-42 and RSA 227-C:4, X, the historical resources council shall, in
3 cooperation with the department of transportation, and with opportunities for comment by former
4 residents of the New Hampshire youth development center (YDC), determine the content for a
5 highwayhistoricalmarkerfortheYDCthatacknowledgestheabusesufferedbyformerresidents.
6 II. The historical resources council shall consider public reports and news articles
7 concerning the hundreds of surviving victims of sexual and physical abuse suffered at the YDC, the
8 deepand lastingpainand traumafor them and their families,oftenincreased bysilence and denials
9 bypublicofficials,andtherepugnanceforsuchabuseandviolationofhumandignityandstatelaws.
10 III. The marker shall be placed after the closure and sale of the YDC property, or no later
11 thanJune30,2028.
12 2 EffectiveDate. Thisactshalltakeeffect60daysafteritspassage.

